    "body": "Here are couple of ideas to get the permissions right:\n\nIdea 1\n\n> handle, path = tempfile.mkstemp()\n> ...\n> umask = os.umask(777)\n> os.umask(umask) <<< Not sure if you need to set the umask back\n> mode = (0o777 & ~umask) <<< I think this is how you translate umask to mode\n> os.chmod(path, mode)\n> ...\n\nIdea 2\n- Use tempfile.mkdtemp() and create empty file instead of tempfile.mkstemp()\n- Delete the directory and file on cleanup\n"
